news.title: PM to distribute sanction letters to PMAY beneficiaries in Jharkhand, Gujarat & Odisha
news.para: ​​The prime minister will also launch the "Awas Plus 24" application that aims at ensuring the allotment of pucca houses by including eligible beneficiaries in the list at the event that will be held in Bhubaneswar.

news.title: NITI Aayog urges centre to do slum rehabilitation on railways, AAI land
news.para: ​​It also calls for rehabilitation of shanty settlements on land owned by other central govt entities such as Airport Authority of India (AAI), ministry of defence and railways to rid the city of slums.

news.title: DDA to keep call centre open on Sept 15 & 16 for housing schemes queries
news.para: According to the statement, bookings for DDA's Sasta Ghar scheme and Madhyam Vargiya scheme started on Tuesday and over 1,400 flats were sold in just three days.

news.title: Arkade Developers raises Rs 122.40 crore from anchor investors ahead of IPO
news.para: According to a regulatory filing, the company has issued 95,62,500 shares to anchor investors at Rs 128 per share, aggregating to Rs 122.40 crore.

news.title: House of Abhinandan Lodha withdraws objectionable Goa advertisement
news.para: Samujjwal Ghosh, chief executive officer (CEO) of the firm, in a letter to the home department, said that the objectionable advertisement referred to in the letter was published on the website of 360 Realtors, one of their channel partners.

news.title: About 12,000 houses to be built under PMAY: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: As per a release from Fadnavis's office, this will be a project of the Maharashtra Housing and Area Development Authority (MHADA) under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY).

news.title: All buildings above 15 meters height in Lucknow to undergo safety audit
news.para: The decision comes in the wake of the collapse of a three-storey building in Transport Nagar last week which claimed eight lives. The building owner was accused of using substandard material in construction.

news.title: Bombay HC orders demolition of seven floors in eight-storey building in Khar
news.para: The Bombay High Court has directed the demolition of seven illegal floors of an eight-storey building in Khar (W), rejecting a plea for regularisation. BMC has been instructed to complete the demolition within three months. The petitioner was fined Rs 50,000 for misleading the court with selective disclosures.

news.title: Lucknow: ED attaches properties worth Rs 29.11 crore in Shine city scam
news.para: The immovable properties attached under the provisions of Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), 2002, include a residential project worth Rs 25.99 crore, commercial property worth Rs 2.10 crore, and agricultural land worth Rs 1.01 crore.

news.title: Gujarat RERA to ease quarterly progress report norms
news.para: ​​The updated rules, expected to be announced soon, will stop the automatic locking of project quarters if the QPR is delayed. Instead, a daily penalty will be implemented to encourage timely submissions. This shift aims to boost compliance among developers, ensuring smoother operations and transparency for homebuyers.

news.title: China bans PwC for six months, fines $62.2 million over Evergrande audit
news.para: The moves by Chinese regulators mark the latest development in a crackdown on PwC for its work with Evergrande, which has become emblematic of a protracted debt crisis in the country's real estate sector.

news.title: Sonam Kapoor’s father-in-law buys $27 million home in London
news.para: The property offering more than 20,000 square feet of space is a short walk from Kensington Gardens and was previously owned by a UK-registered charity and religious order, according to a brochure seen by Bloomberg News.

news.title: BMC floats tender for commercial hub at Mumbai's Dahisar
news.para: According to the BMC's budget document, the primary goal of the hub at Dahisar, and a similar one at Mankhurd, is to provide an integrated bus terminus. This will connect to the city's other transport modes, such as BEST buses and the Metro, while ensuring that intercity and interstate buses terminate at the city's entry points to reduce traffic congestion

news.title: Ambuja Cement's chief manufacturing officer arrested for alleged attempted bribery
news.para: The officer, Rambhav Gattu, offered a flower bouquet and a packet of sweets - later found to contain 200,000 Indian rupees ($2,382) in cash - to the collector of Odisha's Barghar region whose duties include taking in revenues, the directorate said in a statement on Wednesday.

news.title: Large office deals drive commercial absorption across eight cities in H1 2024: Report
news.para: Deals for office spaces above 100,000 sq ft recorded a 54% on-year growth in the first half of calendar year 2024 to 15.69 million sq ft. These deals contributed 45% of the overall commercial transactions, showed data from Knight Frank India.

news.title: HYDRAA urges Hyderabad civic body to freeze property assessments on lake FTLs
news.para: "Encroachers are constructing buildings and then obtaining property assessment numbers. We have written to GHMC asking them not to give property assessment numbers. We have also requested the town planning department not to grant construction permissions on lake FTLs and buffer zones," HYDRAA commissioner AV Ranganath said.

news.title: China set to cut interest rates on $5 trillion of mortgages in September 2024
news.para: Some banks are making final preparations to get ready for the upcoming adjustments on mortgage rates, said the people, asking not to be identified discussing a private matter.

news.title: Kolhapur: 13 stone quarry operators fined Rs 144 crore for illegal mining
news.para: The Kasarwadi gram panchayat had moved a petition before National Green Tribunal (NGT) in 2017, citing environmental violations and illegal stone mining in the village.

news.title: Ahmedabad: SRFDCL issues request for proposal for two riverfront plots
news.para: These plots, located on the west and east banks of the Sabarmati, are set to be developed for mixed-use commercial and recreational purposes, but residential schemes are off-limits.

news.title: Government directs House of Abhinandan Lodha to withdraw 'Conquer Goa' ad
news.para: “I am directed to inform you that it has been brought to the notice of this department that The House of Abhinandan Lodha group has published the advertisement captioned ‘Delhi, Rulers of India, Now Conquer Goa’,” Manesh Kedar, under secretary (home department), said in a letter to the manager of the developer.
